reviewText: Appears to have worked on my VCR which surprised me simply because the component had been unused for years.

Had loose parts rattling around in it , got them out , couldn't see what they were for , extra plastic pins of some kind , didn't work anyway, does not absorb the liquid and machine ejects it after 3 second
Wasted purchase !!  Tape got stuck in VCR (and this never happens with other tapes).  Had to cut it and pull it out.  If I could have given 'NO STARS' I would have.
Cleaning cassette would not come out of the box. I cut the cardboard and got it out. Appears to be in good shape.  I don't know why it wouldnt come out of the box.
After using this item with the liquid provided, my video no longer shows on screen, sound works still.  Not sure if this VCR cleaner caused this or not....
The head cleaner did not work.
this was a piece of junk - fell apart when I tried to use in the VCR  ribbon was loose and wouldn't wind.. piece of junk. Wasted my money
Followed the directions exactly and our VCR is now up and running after being out of commission for about two months. Very happy.
It worked as spected.  I have used similar products before.
Tape got stuck in VCR and the liquid leaked out. Didn't work well at all

The tape came super fast! The flaws the tape had are a loose glass lid and the bottle for the solution had a squirt nozzle that barely worked, so I had to take it off and attempted the drops. When the tape stopped playing, I had trouble ejecting it, so I turned off my TV/VCR combo I inserted the tape in, and after turning it back on, I was able to eject it. After a few minutes of waiting for the player to dry up a bit, I put in a cassette to test the results, and to my amazement, there was a clear picture.
So overall, it is a good product.
